==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Romic
<hw>Rom"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A method of notation
for all spoken sounds, proposed by Mr. Sweet; -- so called because it is
based on the common <xex>Roman</xex>-letter alphabet. It is like the
palaeotype of Mr. Ellis in the general plan, but simpler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Romish</ent>⟦br⟧
